****EDIT**** Actually, I think I see the issue- I started by taking issue with something I think Guzman said, about how more efficent heals help shorten the fight. They don't. Unless maybe the less aggro and less mana usage by the clerics lets them cast nukes, something I don't often see. ****<br>
<br>
I can't be sure if you didn't read/understand my whole post, or if I just can't understand yours.<br>
<br>
Let me explain... no, let me sum up.<br>
<br>
Wars need buffed.<br>
<br>
That sounds to me like what you are saying- You used a cheal chain to tank Vindi, used defensive, and took a similiar DPS to SK. I will note that I said- With Modrod2, and you said you did with without mages. <br>
<br>
But basically you did a similiar fight and took 5% less damage per second (might be wrong, did it in my head), and had more &quot;irregular&quot; damage due to ripostes. That doesn't sound like you did a heck of a lot better then him, in fact, it sounds like he did better then you- More evenly distributed damage, because of no ripostes. Less likely a spike would kill him quicker then the next cheal lands.<br>
<br>
To be clearer, I'm gonna try to seperate the two parts of tanking out for the rest of this post- Absorbing Damage, and Taunt. You have to have both for tanking, and sometimes I use &quot;tanking&quot; to describe both, and sometimes to just describe absorbing damage.<br>
<br>
SK's absorb damage well enough that a cheal chain, especially one backed by Modrod2, can keep them alive.<br>
<br>
SK's taunt well enough that they can lock aggro on them, and let the rest of the raid do more DPS without getting aggro.<br>
<br>
Warriors, without defensive, absorb damage well enough that a cheal chain can keep them alive.<br>
<br>
Warriors, without defe, without EB, taunt well enough that the rest of the raid, if it watches aggro, can do less DPS, but still do DPS.<br>
<br>
Warriors with defensive, absorb damage extremely well. <br>
<br>
Warriors, with defensive, without EB, taunt well enough to keep the aggro off the cheal chain, and the rest of the raid, if it watches it's aggro, can do a small percentage of the DPS it is capable of.<br>
<br>
I cannot really say too much about WITH EB, since I haven't gotten an EB weapon yet, however, several other Warlords in my guild have it. Warriors with EB, defe or not, seem to taunt extremely well, to the point that, especially with Primal Avatar (proc or cast), even SK's have a hard time taunting off them.<br>
<br>
THAT is the problem I have with high end tanking. It simply gimps the entire raid to use a defe warrior on many boss mobs.<br>
<br>
<br>
Here is my most convincing arguement, for me. I'm putting my money where my mouth is. My warlord doesn't log on except by request, and my mage is a week away from modrod2, as long as I give up trying to solo in The Grey- Damned Quad Kiters. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=17853>Cyrz Bloodscale</a>
