but if you want my opinion, VI needs to re-do things so there's 3 tank classes _at any level_ in the game, then give warriors a lot more diversity. better soloing, better grouping, better utility, etc. yes, i know most of you just want to preserve your &quot;main tank&quot; title, but frankly that's unreasonable and at this stage in the game, it's obvious vi is trying to spread out roles so there are no &quot;required&quot; classes. i don't mind warriors taking damage significantly better than sk's so long as it's not so grossly stupid like it was in velious. defensive was the ONLY way to kill things in velious prime, because there was no kei, ae mana, modrod2, etc..., so it was needed for mana to last.<br>
<br>
i think it's reasonable for warriors to take 70% damage, knights 90%, and every other class 100%. that's 10% mitigation for knights, 30% for warriors. if you use the knight numbers as the base-line, then warriors mitigate 22% of the damage knights WOULD be taking in that setup. that's a pretty sizable amount. that means AoW hits a knight for 1038 (causing him to be knight tankable, but only barely...), and a warrior for 807 (which is a much more comfortable margin of error).<br>
<br>
couple this with a much more diversified class setup(for instance, things along the line of the warcry idea would be nice.), fixing mob ac so dualwield/2h is in-line again, and warrior-viable shields...and maybe even throwing in a version of that &quot;intercept-tanking&quot; idea...and you'd be much closer to having a balanced, useful set of classes than now.<br>
<br>
one of the first things that needs to happen, though, is warriors need to realize that just because they aren't required for something doesn't mean their class is broken. i know someone's going to scream that they wouldn't even be required for AoW, but seriously, when was the last time a druid or a necro or a shadowknight or a beastlord was REQUIRED for something? it's an unreasonable mentality to have, and one that most warriors are going to have to accept is changing.<br>
<br>
disagree if you wish, i'm just an idealist that's hoping we can have EVERYONE useful, but NOT REQUIRED in the end. i'd be much more interested in having a good discussion about what we can agree on than arguing vehemently, though.<br>
<br>
P.S. the aggro spells on test are lame, stop mentioning them. i'd be happier if they just tossed them in the trash. note i can already hold aggro without turning attack on, and i REALLY DON'T want to turn into a buffing class that gets to aggroize the main tank every 10 minutes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uzumbukfleshcarver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zumbuk Fleshcarver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/4/02 1:54:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1190.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> Bleh..I had a response typed out...but I said to hell with it. Im too tired to even argue.<br>
